TY  - JOUR
T1  - Day Care and Selected Employee Work Behaviors
AU  - Milkovich, George T.
AU  - Gomez, Luis R.
Y1  - 1976/03/01
PY  - 1976
DA  - 1976/03/01
N1  - doi: 10.5465/255451
DO  - 10.5465/255451
T2  - Academy of Management Journal
JF  - Academy of Management Journal
JO  - AMJ
SP  - 111
EP  - 115
VL  - 19
IS  - 1
PB  - Academy of Management
N2  - The article presents findings of a study on the relationship of day care to selected employee work behaviors in the U.S. The data for this study were gathered at the Northside Child Development Center in Minneapolis. The work behaviors of 90 subjects were collected for 20 months. Three indices of work behavior considered were absenteeism, turnover, and job performance. Examination of the monthly turnover and absentee rates revealed that the rates of absenteeism for nonparticipants exhibit greater variability than those for participants or employees in general.
AB  - The article presents findings of a study on the relationship of day care to selected employee work behaviors in the U.S. The data for this study were gathered at the Northside Child Development Center in Minneapolis. The work behaviors of 90 subjects were collected for 20 months. Three indices of work behavior considered were absenteeism, turnover, and job performance. Examination of the monthly turnover and absentee rates revealed that the rates of absenteeism for nonparticipants exhibit greater variability than those for participants or employees in general.
SN  - 0001-4273
M3  - doi: 10.5465/255451
UR  - https://doi.org/10.5465/255451
