TY  - JOUR
T1  - Operations Management in Selected Nonmanufacturing Organizations
AU  - Morey, Russell
Y1  - 1976/03/01
PY  - 1976
DA  - 1976/03/01
N1  - doi: 10.5465/255453
DO  - 10.5465/255453
T2  - Academy of Management Journal
JF  - Academy of Management Journal
JO  - AMJ
SP  - 120
EP  - 124
VL  - 19
IS  - 1
PB  - Academy of Management
N2  - The article presents findings of a study which compared the characteristics of operations management in three non-manufacturing organizations. Three organizations were used in the study: a hospital, a university, and a retail firm. Interviews were conducted with each operations manager, as defined by each organization, and with all department heads included in operations management. There were major differences in the subfunctions composing the operations department in the three organizations. The operations managers and their department heads emphasized the significance of their basic raw material or input relative to the transformation process.
AB  - The article presents findings of a study which compared the characteristics of operations management in three non-manufacturing organizations. Three organizations were used in the study: a hospital, a university, and a retail firm. Interviews were conducted with each operations manager, as defined by each organization, and with all department heads included in operations management. There were major differences in the subfunctions composing the operations department in the three organizations. The operations managers and their department heads emphasized the significance of their basic raw material or input relative to the transformation process.
SN  - 0001-4273
M3  - doi: 10.5465/255453
UR  - https://doi.org/10.5465/255453
Y2  - 2026/04/24
