PB  - Academy of Management
N2  - Data collected from black and white workers in three organizations indicate that workers living in communities with different perceived levels of prosperity have different job satisfaction. A relatively less affluent community seems to be a causal variable in lower job satisfaction of workers. The implications of these findings on workers' behavior are discussed.
